wiki.summary: "Trustfall" is a song by American singer P!nk, released as the second single from her eponymous ninth studio album on January 27, 2023. It was co-written by P!nk with Johnny McDaid and Fred Again.., who also both produced the song. The song contains a "driving EDM beat" and "emotionally fraught lyrics" about confronting fear and trusting things will work out. The track's music video was released the same day as the song, and directed by Georgia Hudson. Read more on Last.fm.
wiki.content: "Trustfall" is a song by American singer P!nk, released as the second single from her eponymous ninth studio album on January 27, 2023. It was co-written by P!nk with Johnny McDaid and Fred Again.., who also both produced the song. The song contains a "driving EDM beat" and "emotionally fraught lyrics" about confronting fear and trusting things will work out. The track's music video was released the same day as the song, and directed by Georgia Hudson. It stars P!nk and a young woman who is trying to find the confidence to talk to a man she is interested in at a house party. P!nk also stands atop a hotel and dances on a dark street, which was choreographed by Ryan Heffington. Read more on Last.fm.
